ttention if they experience symptoms that could indicate the occurrence of torsade de pointes such as dizziness, lightheadedness, fainting, palpitations, irregular heartbeat, shortness of breath, or syncope. Because of the drug''s long half-life, adverse reactions including a prolonged QT interval may not resolve quickly, thus appropriate monitoring is necessary.', 'Synergism', 'The use of vandetanib in combination with other medications that can prolong the QT interval should generally be avoided.', 'Major', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/88986/', '', 'Lidocaine, Tocainide, Mexiletine, Bretylium, Moricizine', 'Acalabrutinib, Dacomitinib, Pexidartinib, Tepotinib, Avapritinib, Selumetinib, Cobimetinib, Capmatinib, Ibrutinib, Afatinib, Tivozanib, More', 1767369485);
